   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   COLON-CANCER (Undated) _ Studies have shown that fewer than 41
percent of Americans over 50 have ever been tested for colon
cancer. Even more disturbing is a recent government report that
only 9 percent of Medicare beneficiaries get the annual recommended
fecal occult blood test, one of the most basic screening tools.
``Women know about mammography, men know about prostate
screening,'' says Dr. Moshe Shaike of Memorial Sloan-Kettering in
New York. ``People are a little bit squeamish about intestines,
stool and having an examination in this area.'' By SYLVIA WOOD.
</P>
<P>
   FREDERICK'S (Hollwood) _Today's Frederick's of Hollywood is
about flirtation, not sleaze. By CYNTHIA ROBINS.
</P>
