49ers had had Steve Young and Garrison Hearst healthy for the
entire season, they might have been a playoff team once again.
That's the opinion of the man who lost a bid to become club
president and fled to Cleveland, Dwight Clark, now vice president
and general manager of the Cleveland Browns. By JOHN CRUMPACKER.
