when I converted to Catholicism. To us, the women and men for whom
the Washington Square Bar and Grill was more second home than
saloon, it was _ and always will be _ ``the Square.'' After 27
years in business under three separate owners, the Square closed
its doors forever this week. The times and people's eating and
drinking habits have changed, said the final owner, Peter Osborne.
By STEPHANIE SALTER.
