   FBI-INTERNET-CRIME (Washington) _ FBI Director Louis Freeh tells
Congress that law enforcement agencies need more legal powers to
prosecute Internet criminals, including hackers and thieves. He
says the law should be changed to allow suspects as young as 15 to
be prosecuted in federal courts. By AUSTIN ZALKIN. Story will also
be filed in the ``f,'' or financial-business news category.
</P>
