<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN _ First impressions are important, and in politics
early images of the candidates are often hard to shake no matter
how inaccurate they are. Vice President Al Gore is stuck with the
wooden bit, and Gov. George W. Bush is forever a dim bulb. Yet both
men are more complex than their images. Gore can be witty, and Bush
is smarter than you think. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
