become one of the most sought-after wine-producing regions in the
world. Not by wine drinkers, except for a handful of smart folk,
but by big producers from the north who are buying hundreds of
acres of vineyard land and importers from Britain and the United
States who are finding good affordable wines. By Frank J. Prial.
