<P>
   &UR; THE CHANGING FACE OF HOLLYWOOD'S LEADING MEN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEW-KINGS-HOLLYWOOD-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Something very odd is happening to the image of Tinseltown's
leading man. Just take a look at the list of best-actor nominees at
Sunday night's Academy Awards ceremony. Of the five, only Denzel
Washington is true matinee-idol material. The others, not so long
ago, would have been placed firmly in the category of character
actors, not leads. But whereas the character actors are triumphing,
the more conventional leading men of Hollywood seem to be treading
water or even floundering badly....By Andrew Gumbel, The
Independent &QL;
</P>
