   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   CMBUY _ The rapidly growing owner of Variety and other trade
magazines has agreed to buy Atlanta-based CMD Group Inc. for $299.5
million, the companies said Tuesday. CMD, formerly called
Construction Market Data Group, operates construction trade
publications and provides national and regional directories and
other data on the industry in print and on its Internet sites.
(Grantham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS-FUTURE _It was a harsh message, but they took it well.
Gary Hamel, a Harvard business strategist told leaders of Emory's
Goizueta Business School that the days are numbered for old
business approaches and traditional business colleges on campuses.
The ``branding'' of business
</P>
<P>
   training by schools like Emory and Harvard will wane, he said,
and give way to new interactive online education taught by the best
minds _ and business schools had better brace for it. (Holsendolph,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ISS-KLAUS _ Chris Klaus, the 26-year-old entreprenuer who
founded ISS in his Georgia Tech dorm room, has given $15 million to
his alma mater to build an advanced computing center. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUTOMOTIVE
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS _ EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the
current week.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0328: 2000 HONDA S2000 Roadster _ Honda's sporty
new convertible brings a smile to performance enthusiasts. The all
new and virtually hand-built head-turner comes with all the
characteristics of a genuine sports car. It even has a push-button
starter. (DeVault, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes
4-column color photo of the 2000 Honda S2000 and a 18-pica color
photo of the car's push-button starter.
