<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA _ Women live longer and have less money than
men, so they need to be better investors. The good news is that
women are better investors. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MANSION-DWELLERS _ Your Internet company's IPO makes you a
gazillionaire, and you buy a giant house. Then what? Then, you
might call Mike Adams. Adams, himself a hard-charging entrepreneur,
makes a living serving the newly rich by staffing their mansions
with chefs, gardeners, pool boys, whatever they need. (Scott,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
