u a BC-SPACEPORT-TEXAS-HNS &LR;      03-28 0443
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPACEPORT-TEXAS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COUNTY OFFICIALS CREATE PARTNERSHIP TO ATTRACT SPACEPORT TO EAST
TEXAS 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Attn: Calif., Fla.)  
(Eds.: Kenedy County is cq) 
 
By STEVE OLAFSON 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANGLETON, Texas _ Brazoria County Commissioners Court on Tuesday
created a spaceport authority that can acquire property and issue
revenue bonds.
</P>
<P>
   The Gulf Coast Regional Spaceport Development Corp., approved
unanimously by the court, is designed to attract the budding
commercial space market.
</P>
<P>
   ``It shows the region's and the county's commitment,'' Fred
Welch, executive director of Brazoria County Partnership Inc., said
after the vote. The partnership is the county economic development
agency.
</P>
<P>
   The spaceport authority is competing with Kenedy County in South
Texas and sites in Florida for a commercial spaceport where
reusable rockets would deliver commercial satellites into space to
orbit Earth.
</P>
<P>
   Brazoria County officials are focusing their efforts on a
California-based company, Space Access, which plans to use a space
vehicle that takes off from a runway like an airplane, Welch said.
</P>
<P>
   A consortium headed by Lockheed Martin also is planning a
commercial spaceport, but its efforts have been slowed by technical
problems with the design of its vertical-launch rocket, Welch said.
</P>
<P>
   Brazoria County officials have held talks with Dow Chemical Co.
about buying a 4,000-acre site near the town of Oyster Creek for
the spaceport.
</P>
<P>
   Oyster Creek, a city of 1,100 people in Brazoria County, is
about 50 miles south of downtown Houston.
</P>
<P>
   After the spaceport authority's board of directors is named and
articles of incorporation are approved in two weeks, the agency can
issue a letter of commitment to buy the Dow property and begin the
engineering and environmental studies needed to win a license from
the Federal Aviation Administration.
</P>
<P>
   Up to $300 million in revenue bonds may be needed to build a
spaceport, but that figure could be reduced to $60 million to $80
million if Congress approves legislation to provide federal loan
guarantees for communications satellites, Welch said. He noted that
such guarantees would attract private investors.
</P>
<P>
   Plans for the spaceport call for a 12,000-foot runway and about
900,000 square feet of manufacturing and administrative space. The
project would create several thousands jobs.
</P>
<P>
   A decision by Space Access, headquartered in Palmdale, Calif.,
on the location of its spaceport is expected this year.
</P>
<P>
   ``It could be as early as July and as late as December,'' Welch
said.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY XXXX &QL; 
$$$
</P>
