<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, MARCH 29
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-RUSSIA-ELCTION-NYT (moved on Friday, March 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, March 24,
about reports by the state-owned ORT television network that a
candidate in the Russian presidential election was supported by
Jews, homosexuals and foreigners misstated the affiliation of Igor
Malashenko, a media executive who commented. He works for Vladimir
V. Gusinsky, who is chairman of Media Most, the conglomerate that
includes the independent NTV network. He does not work for Boris A.
Berezovsky, a major partner in the state-owned channel.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-WESTBANK-NYT (moved on Tuesday, March 21)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, March 21,
about Yosef Bienenstock, a boyhood friend of Pope John Paul II who
now lives in Israel, misidentified the biblical source of the
inscription on the tombstone of Bienenstock's brother _ ``And I
shall raise you from your graves, my people, and I shall bring you
to the land of Israel.'' It is Ezekiel, not Jeremiah.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-MAGEE-NYT (moved on Friday, March 24)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Warren Magee, sent by the New York Times News
Service on Friday, March 24, misstated his place of death. It was
Tampa, Fla.; he had practiced in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBITS-NYT (moved on Monday, March 27)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Albert R. Connelly, sent by the New York Times
News Service on Monday, March 27, misstated his birthdate. It was
March 24, 1908, not Nov. 24.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-EVERHART-NYT (moved on Sunday, March 19)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Rex Everhart sent by the New York Times News
Service on Sunday, March 19, misspelled the name of his birthplace.
It is Watseka, Ill., not Wateska.
